I looked over at my ex's face was super red with embarrassment and realized that it was actually true. I felt a serious rush of ego boost, but at the same time, I felt something unexpected too. Weeks went by and on the last day of the month, she walked into Waffle House with a huge smile on her face. I walked over with her usual order and sat beside her in the booth. She asked me, If I would finally be her boyfriend again. I smiled back and said, absolutely not. I reminded her that she cheated on me with several guys and one of them was my best friend. She picked up the glass of water and thought about splashing it all over me. Instead, she splashed water on her own face to wake herself up and left, angrily ripping up one of the menus in the restaurant out of frustration before walking out the front door. The entire angry scene was crazy cute, like, ah, there goes my little Harley Quinn. I grinned and told my manager that I was finally quitting. To this day, we're still together and no longer the toxic kids we used to be. Also for our prenup, we had a fun photo shoot at that same Waffle House, forever reminding us of our ridiculous and petty days.

In one desperate moment, when mom turned for more dye, Katie scooped bleach and smeared it across Mom's eyes. Mom's Scream was inhuman as she clawed at her face. Those minutes waiting for sirens felt like hours. When they finally broke down Daniela's door, they found mom sitting calmly on the bed, brushing both Katie's hair and the dolls. My two danielas have finally met, she announced it's proudly. The little girl's mom placed a restraining order on our family and Mom's been institutionalized 8 months now. Last time I visited, she grabbed my hand and whispered, I forgive you for sending Daniela away again. After that, dad and I cleaned out Daniela's room together and donated everything, including that horrible doll.

The man's lightning spell struck instantly, wiping out all the Red flying insects on the map. Just as he thought the battle was over, a giant abissal worm burst from underground and bit red hair. The massive worm was instantly killed by his sacrificial heavy strike, while red hair, as the Academy's top support mage, had long since cast a protective barrier around himself. The man's spell reminded him of their Academy days when they reached the 68th floor of the dungeon and were completely helpless against the boss, only to have him arrive late and instantly obliterated with a full element magic spell. Now that he had returned to the team, their combined strength meant they could break records once again.
